# Automatic Internal Linking (SEO)

## Required links
- **Broker review pages**: add links to relevant comparison pages (`/compare/{a}-vs-{b}/`) using **keyword-rich anchor text**.
- **Comparison pages**: always link back to both broker review pages with descriptive anchors.
- **Blog articles (guides + news posts)**: include a “Related broker reviews” block that links to relevant broker pages (prefer brokers mentioned in the article; otherwise top-rated brokers for evergreen guides/news).
- **Broker pages**: include a **“Related brokers”** section near the bottom (3 brokers max).

## Anchor text rules
- Prefer anchors like:
  - “Compare {A} vs {B} (fees, platforms & safety)”
  - “Read {Broker} review (fees, platforms & safety)”
- Avoid generic anchors like “click here” or “read more”.

## Implementation rules (static sites)
- Internal links should be **pretty URLs** (folder routes ending with `/`), not `.html`.
- Keep changes **idempotent** when injecting blocks (use HTML markers like `RELATED_BROKER_REVIEWS:START/END`).
- When generating compare pages, create **one page per broker pair** for each site.

